  "prompt": "What is 3E - 3 tier AC in Duronto?",
  "response": "In the context of Indian Railways, \"3E\" refers to the Three-Tier Executive class of accommodation in trains like Duronto Express. Duronto Express trains are known for their faster service and fewer stops compared to regular trains, and they primarily focus on long-distance, higher-speed travel.\n\nThe \"3E\" designation means that passengers in this class are accommodated in three tiers (levels) of sleeper berths. The \"Executive\" designation indicates a higher level of comfort and amenities compared to regular sleeper classes. In the 3E class, the coaches typically have cushioned berths, air conditioning, and improved onboard services.\n\nOn the other hand, \"3 Tier AC\" (Air Conditioned Three Tier) is a standard designation used across various classes in Indian Railways for three-tier sleeper coaches that are air-conditioned but may not provide the same level of amenities as the Executive class.\n\nIn summary, \"3E\" is a specific type of three-tier AC accommodation that aims to provide a more luxurious experience for travelers compared to standard 3 Tier AC.",
